article.headline: Manhattan 87, Iona 68
article.story: NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. (AP) -- Arturo Dubois had 21 points and 14 rebounds and Manhattan placed five players in double figures in an 87-68 win over Iona on Friday night. Jeff Xavier had 20 points and C.J. Anderson added 19 for the Jaspers (7-4, 3-0 Metro-Atlantic Athletic Conference), who have won seven straight. Manhattan led 37-36 at halftime and never trailed. The Jaspers built a 12-point lead midway through the second half and then went on an 8-0 run to put it away. Ricky Soliver scored 17 of his 26 points in the first half for Iona (8-3, 2-1), which finished 10-for-17 from the free-throw line. Steve Burtt, who came in averaging 23.6 points, was just 4-of-17 from the field and scored 14. The Gaels also committed 18 turnovers.
